OL,3,CHillsborough Law to prevent cover-ups
OL,4,C'must be all or nothing', campaigners
OL,5,Csay
OL,7,FHome Secretary Yvette Cooper has
OL,8,Fdefended the delay over the proposed
OL,9,FHillsborough Law, as the Government's
OL,10,Fself-imposed deadline to introduce the
OL,11,Flaw to Parliament nears.
OL,13,FFamilies of those affected by other
OL,14,Ftragedies and scandals are also in
OL,15,Fsupport of the proposed law, including
OL,16,FAmos Waldman from Covid-19 Bereaved
OL,17,FFamilies for Justice UK (CBFFJ).
OL,19,FHe views the duty of candour as the
OL,20,Fmost important part of the bill and
OL,21,Fthat "nothing less will do".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G14/19
